Connector::Multi::YAML
.SH "Description"
.IX Header "Description"
This is a glue connector to create the required reference syntax for
Connector::Multi based on a backend configuration handled by \s-1YAML.\s0
.PP
\&\s-1LOCATION\s0 is passed over as file to load by \s-1YAML.\s0
.PP
Internally, the constructor walks down the whole tree and translates
all keys starting or ending with the \*(L"@\*(R" character into references as
understood by Connector::Multi.
.SH "CONFIGURATION"
.IX Header "CONFIGURATION"
There is no special configuration besides the mandatory \s-1LOCATION\s0 property.
.SH "Example"
.IX Header "Example"
.Vb 3
\&   my $backend = Connector::Multi::YAML\->new({
\&       LOCATION = /etc/myconfig.yaml
\&   })
\&
\&   my $multi = Connector::Multi\->new({
\&       BASECONNECTOR => $backend
\&   })
